&lt;p&gt;Use Session variables, just as you have alluded. They aren't just used by login pages, they are used by everything. Sessions are the equivalent of server-side cookies / server-side storage, so you don't have to worry (as much) about your users tampering with them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to make life more difficult for yourself, you can json encode your variables and store them as an object in a database or even flat text file. But really, read up on sessions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All you need to know is &lt;code&gt;session_start();&lt;/code&gt; before anything else then &lt;code&gt;$_SESSION['var']=$yourvar;&lt;/code&gt; to save data and &lt;code&gt;$_SESSION['yourvar']&lt;/code&gt; to retrieve it later (such as on another page).&lt;/p&gt;
